WDYT:
```scala
class ExcludedPackagesHandler(pkgs: List[String]) {
  private var cached: List[String] = prepareCache(pkgs)

  private def prepareCache(pkgs: List[String]): List[String] = ...

  def update(pkgs: List[String]): Unit = {cached = prepareCache(pkgs) }

  def isExcluded(pkg: String): Boolean = cached.exists(excluded => pkg.startsWith(excluded))
}
// instead of clear we would call update with new userExcludedPackages
```

this way in 'isExcluded' we don't have to always convert ListBuffer->List, pattern match etc. it focuses on simplifying this method.
